mainText: The list since 2000 includes Toronto’s Bryan Berard, who was struck in the eye with a stick that year and underwent seven eye surgeries the next season to make his comeback; Calgary’s Al MacInnis, who was struck in the eye by a high stick in 2001 and, two years later, had to sit out when the retina in the same eye became detached; Detroit’s Steve Yzerman, who fractured his cheekbone and scratched a cornea when struck by a puck in 2004; Toronto’s Mats Sundin, who was struck in the left eye by a puck that fractured his orbital bone in 2005; Washington’s Tom Poti, who in 2010 took a shot to the face and needed four plates inserted into his shattered cheekbone and orbital bone; Philadelphia’s Ian Laperriere, who in 2010 took a slap shot to the face that broke his orbital bone and gave him a concussion that eventually forced him to retire; Vancouver’s Manny Malhotra, who underwent two eye surgeries after being struck by a puck in 2011 but managed to return; and Pronger, who has been out with concussion symptoms for more than a year and which may be related to the eye injury he sustained.
